          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The direction of a polar pattern is relative to the orientation of the data source. For example, you can use the cardioid pattern with a back-facing data source to more clearly record sound from behind the device, or with a front-facing data source to more clearly record sound from in front of the device (such as the user’s voice)."
            }
          ]
        },
